- however, at tryouts my arm hurt way too much to play baseball at my best so I unfortunately didn’t make the team

- so my insurance is shit and didn’t want to fund the surgery until all other options were exhausted, so I spent the next 4 months in a cast to see if the ligaments would heal themselves, and they didn’t
- so I had to get surgery on my wrist, which i did in november of senior year
- during the surgery the anesthesiologist had to call a cardio surgeon to monitor me, because he noticed a weird pattern on the heart monitor
- then the cardio surgeon was like you need to see a cardiologist ASAP
- so we went to the cardiologist and they were like yeah you have this thing called wolfe parkinson white syndrome and you are lucky to still be alive
- so then i have to take it easy for a couple months with a heart monitor on at all times until I recover from the first surgery
- then i go get my heart surgery april of senior year
- apparently I clinically died twice during the process
- anyway all is well since then luckily the surgery fixed whatever the problem was but I still go back like once a month to make sure. 
- Remember how I said my broken arm didn’t heal correctly? well yeah

- so i had to make a choice, either take the chance that my wrist won’t deteriorate and become unusable and in pain all the time, or be in mild pain when I lift heavy things for the rest of my life.
- I decided to not take the chance and get my arm rebroken and put back together the right way
- now my arm is still in pain when I try to lift heavy things but my wrist thankfully no longer hurts
- oh I also have permanent nerve damage in two of my fingers on my right hand so I can’t feel anything lol
